               <p>1099. <persName id="def1-1099-18350406" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1099-18350406" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1099-18350406" type="age" value="24"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1099-18350406" type="surname" value="STEVENS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1099-18350406" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">CHARLES STEVENS</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18350406-1099-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18350406-1099-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="royalOffences"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18350406-1099-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="coiningOffences"></interp>for a misdemeanor.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. SHEA</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">conducted the Prosecution</hi>.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350406-name-1317" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1317" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1317" type="surname" value="ROUCH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1317" type="given" value="FREDERICK"></interp>FREDERICK ROUCH</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a cheesemonger's shop, on Deptford-bridge, at Greenwich. On the 11th of September, about seven o'clock in the evening, the prisoner came into my shop for a quarter of a pound of Che<lb></lb>shire cheese—I served him—it came to 3<hi rend="italic">d</hi>., or 3 1/2 <hi rend="italic">d</hi>.—he said it was rather</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183504060199"></xptr>
               <p>more than he wanted—I told him it would not spoil, and he could put it into his pocket—he gave me half-a-crown—I put it on the ledge, not in the till—I gave him the change—he went out, and in about five minutes he returned, for some more cheese—I said, "I thought I cut you too much before"—he said, "A friend of mine has got that, and I want a quarter of a pound more for myself"—I served him, and he threw down another half-crown—I said, "It is a bad one"—he said, "No such thing"—I said, "Look at it, it is bad"—it then struck me that the other half-crown was bad—I looked at it, and it was, bad—I said to him, "You gave me a bad half-crown five minutes ago"—he said he had not been in the shop before—I went round to him, and said, "I am awkwardly situated, having no shopman here; if you will give me up the change, I will let you go"—he said he had not been there before—I called in a policeman, and gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350406-name-1318" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1318" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1318" type="surname" value="DYKE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1318" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM DYKE</persName>
                  </hi>. I was called in, and took the prisoner—I received these two half-crowns from the prosecutor.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350406-name-1319" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1319" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1319" type="surname" value="FIELD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350406-name-1319" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN FIELD</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of counterfeit coin to the Mint. These half-crown pieces are both counterfeit, and cast in the same mould.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I leave it to yourselves to say whether it stands to reason that I should go to his shop and offer two half-crowns within five minutes.</p>
               <p>
